snippet.textDisplay: 2 TIMOTHY 4 VERSE 3 SAYS,  For the time will come when people will not put up with sound doctrine. Instead, to suit their own desires, they will gather around them a great number of teachers to say what their itching ears want to hear. I've read quite a few comments and for anyone who has the guts to read this pay attention to the scripture above. People somehow, someway have the notion that you can be a good person, with a good character,  with a good heart, and this will get you in heaven. You can be the type of person that gives money to worthy causes, you can be a person that inspires people, or you can have a special ability rather if it's singing, or an athlete or a exceptional business mind making large sums of money and this will get you in heaven. That's what the 'itching ears' reference means. 'Sound Doctrine' says that Jesus is the only way to the Father. That you must ask Jesus to come into your life, be the savior of your soul, the Lord of your life, and then you must do your best to live holy.That means spending time with him, rather if its in church or reading your bible so that you won't be fooled by false teachings. Jesus said, "If you deny or reject me before men, I will deny or reject you before my Father in heaven." Some one said Kobe ain't dead, he got drafted to heaven's team. I never heard Kobe say anything about Jesus. I never heard Kobe say anything about his salvation. I never head Kobe mention he was a follower of Christ. I never heard him say anything about the one, the ONLY one that can wash away your sins. OH yes he had faith being a Catholic, but faith without works is dead. And Faith in God does not get you into heaven. Giving your life to Jesus does. Why is it that we have been brainwashed thinking their is no such place called Hell? We only want to hear people say when someone dies that their in a better place, or that their looking down at us. But if you read the story about Lazarus and the Rich man, the bible says in Sheol or Hades his eyes lifted up. He saw Lazarus in Abraham's bosom and cried out, "Father Abraham!! Tell Lazarus to dip his finger in water so that the drops can cool my tongue, for I am an agony!! No one wants to respond to what I'm saying because the truth can not be changed. IF Kobe did not accept Jesus then he is in hell!! He is trapped in the flames of hell! He can never come back from hell! He will be in torment day and night for ever. in Hell. And after Judgement, he will be thrown into the lake of fire. And not just Kobe but all that were with him, if they did not accept Jesus, they are in Hell right along Kobe. The only way to rest in peace is to call on the name of Jesus to save your soul. For in Hell there is NO rest!!

snippet.textDisplay:
I am italian.
I've never seen an NBA match, I've never seen a Lakers match.
But in the nineties, basketball was a huge thing, and there were 3 names that we all knew:

Michael Jordan, Kobe Bryant, Shaquille O'Neal (and later, LeBron James, but it was already 2000's).

These were giants of the NBA.
Everybody knew about them.
Sunday evening I was at dinner with friends and colleagues, when one of them, looking at his phone, said "Kobe Bryant is dead?".
Me and him were the ONLY people, at that table, who knew who he was.
The news was shocking.
It was so sudden.
Too soon, just too soon.
That's... not how you should die. Just no.
